==Hyphenation==
Ar·ma·ged·don ( Noun )


'''Definition:'''
* '''1.''' The scene of a decisive conflict on a great scale.
* '''2.''' The place where the final battle will be fought between the forces of [[good]] and [[evil]].
* '''3.''' Any great and crucial conflict.

'''Etymology:'''
* '''[http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Revelation Revelations 16:16] (Battlefield of [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mount_Megiddo Megiddo])''' "The place of the last battle at the Day of Judgement."

